Yeah, because doing the exact thing someone asked you not to do is the definition of "paying tribute" to someone. JJ didn't want his songs sung, yet that's exactly what they did here.
Well sung and executed, no doubt. But I'd have respected Coke Studio more had they not marketed this as a tribute to JJ.
